-- Arson Blamed for Southern Chile Fire That Killed Six at CMPC
-- B y   R a n d a l l   W o o d s
-- 2012-01-06T10:24:43Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-06/arson-blamed-for-southern-chile-fire-that-killed-six-at-cmpc.html
Empresas CMPC SA,  Chile ’s second-
largest pulp exporter, said a forest fire that killed six
firefighters and injured two in the country’s south was started
by arsonists, Chief Executive Officer Hernan Rodriguez said
yesterday.  The company notified authorities “opportunely” of the
fires, which broke out simultaneously at 50 points, he said in a
statement e-mailed yesterday evening.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Randall Woods in Santiago at 
